10/4/00
  Overnight test: two Harmonic channels, one with single ad, other with
    2 ads back to back.  Output at 12 Mbps.
  Result: both channels still running, without any reset.  But have some
    timeout and forced switch. 

  BUG: Closing B warning message for IPPP... sequence is fixed.

  Try working on using the local time base for output in view ytse-dpi2

  New time base management scheme:
    Each channel keeps an tbOffset and outTbOffset.  The tbOffset is used
    to keep track between the phase differernce between input PCR and local
    clock.  It is used to response to the PTS Offset Req from PPC.
    The outTbOffset is added to the input PTS/DTS to form output PTS/DTS.
    It remains constant for the entire channel on time.
    At splice point, outTbOffset is computed so that the PTS/DTS would be
    continuous accross splice point.
    Note: Theoretically, we should also recalculate outTbOffset
          when the time base discontinuity flag is set!


