10/9/00
  Weekend test: both channel still running

  ytse-dpi: reduced EOS test
  ytse-dpi2: time base test
  ytse-rc: not used
  ytse-sp: using this for bug fix

  Need to debug latest bad pidbuf pointer problem -> dpi1064.fls
  Seems like the problem only happens when DBG_AUDIO is off!
  Wayne is looking into the problem.
  Problem found and fixed.  Wayne checked in some new changes with bugs last
  Thrus which caused the problem.

  Reuse ytse-sp view for Smart EOS insertion test.

  Smart EOS insertion:
    Do not append EOS to a picture.  Instead, add EOS TP to the beginning
    of the first picture in the new channel.
    This scheme works!  Code checked in.
 
  Time base handling:
    Several approaches:
      - no mapping, but allow time base discontinuity
      - mapped to offset-adjusted input time base
      - mapped to local time base

    Method:
      - regeneration of missing time stamps (in input time base: inPts, inDts)
      - offset/mapping for splice decision (inPts, inDts => pts, dts)
      - offset/mapping for outpu (inPts, inDts => pts, dts)
      - time base dicsontinuity bit setting

    Variables:
      inPts, inDts: for storing input and regenerated missing PTS/DTS
      pts, dts: mapped to local time base for splice decision
                mapped to output timestamps based on selected time base mode
                  for output to statmux
      PcrChanInfo::tbOffset: used for third mode
      outTbOffset: used for second mode

    Questions:
      - which time base should det, pet be in?  How about prevDet, refTime?
      - pet is now in local time base


